               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390617-name-1481" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1481" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1481" type="surname" value="BEDSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1481" type="given" value="DAVID"></interp>DAVID BEDSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a constable of Corydon—the prosecutor lives at Norwood. On the 29th of April I was on duty at a quarter to one o'clock in the morning, and stopped the prisoner about three quarters of a mile from the prosecutor's house—he was moving goods—he had as many things as you could wheel in a barrow—the two pails and the horsecloth, which were among the things, were claimed by his master.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183906170277"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390617-name-1482" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1482" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1482" type="surname" value="MOSELY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390617-name-1482" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH MOSELY</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Norwood, and am a coach-proprietor. The prisoner lived with me four years as a horse-keeper—he had left me in October—I frequently missed pails and horsecloths, but I did not suspect him—I believe he was out of employ—these things are mine—they have my name on them.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> These two pails I used while I wan with him in carrying water home—I forgot to take them back, and the cloth I <hi rend="italic">chucked</hi> on my shoulder, because it rained—I forgot to take it back. <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18390617-1989-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
